# Gomoku Game User Manual

Welcome to the Gomoku game! This manual will guide you through the installation process and explain how to play the game.

## Table of Contents
1. [Installation](#installation)
2. [Game Rules](#game-rules)
3. [Playing the Game](#playing-the-game)
4. [Resetting the Game](#resetting-the-game)

## 1. Installation <a name="installation"></a>

To play the Gomoku game, you need to have Python and the required dependencies installed on your machine. Follow the steps below to install the necessary environment:

1. Open your terminal or command prompt.
2. Navigate to the directory where you have saved the game files.
3. Run the following command to install the required dependencies:

```shell
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Once the installation is complete, you are ready to play the game!

## 2. Game Rules <a name="game-rules"></a>

Gomoku is a two-player strategy board game. The objective of the game is to be the first player to form a horizontal, vertical, or diagonal line of five consecutive pieces on the game board.

## 3. Playing the Game <a name="playing-the-game"></a>

To start the game, follow these steps:

1. Open your terminal or command prompt.
2. Navigate to the directory where you have saved the game files.
3. Run the following command to start the game:

```shell
python main.py
```

4. A game window will appear with a 15x15 grid.
5. Players take turns placing their pieces on the grid by clicking on the desired cell.
6. The first player to form a line of five consecutive pieces wins the game.
7. If no player forms a line of five consecutive pieces and the grid is full, the game ends in a draw.

## 4. Resetting the Game <a name="resetting-the-game"></a>

To reset the game and start a new round, follow these steps:

1. Click on the "Game" menu in the game window.
2. Select "Reset" from the dropdown menu.
3. The game board will be cleared, and a new round will begin.

That's it! You are now ready to enjoy playing the Gomoku game. Have fun and may the best player win!

